+# 0.8.3 — Mem0-parity resolution report
+
+> **Status: Slice 10 (D0b) PHASE A complete — pipeline built + validated; the
+> citable per-class priced gap awaits Phase-B authorization (orchestrator/HITL).**
+> The numbers below from the cheap-validate / pilot are *pipeline-proof* runs on tiny
+> subsets (8 and 12 questions), **not** the citable per-class parity verdict. The
+> power-sized priced pass (606 q) is Phase B.
+
+## Slice 10 (D0b) — the target: FathomDB − {Mem0, Graphiti/Zep, naive-RAG} per class
+
+Two-level measurement (design §2/§4): external per-class `FathomDB − {mem0_oss,
+graphiti_zep, naive_rag}` on (a) strict full-gold Recall@K ($0) and (b)
+identical-answerer accuracy (priced, gpt-5.4). Gold = re-pinned LME-derived,
+`repin_hash 2916cace`, all four classes ≥ 150. Runner: `eval/d0b_parity_run.py`
+(resilient: atomic checkpoint + auto-resume + backoff + completeness guard +
+window-fit); verdict via the frozen `decide_083`.
+
+### Phase-A pipeline validation (this spawn — NOT the citable gap)
+
+- **Pipeline works end-to-end.** Cheap-validate (gemini-flash-lite, 8 q × all 4
+  classes, 3 arms): all arms ran, recall + accuracy → per-class deltas + paired CI +
+  MDE, atomic checkpoint + live resume verified, `decide_083` emitted a mechanical
+  verdict. completeness 1.0. `runs/0.8.3-d0b-cheapval.json`.
+- **Priced path works.** Pilot (gpt-5.4, 12 q, 3 arms): 36 calls, 0 errors,
+  completeness 1.0, `decide_083` emitted. `runs/0.8.3-d0b-pilot.json`.
+- **Resume proven before spend** (kill/restart unit test: re-calls ONLY absent cells,
+  zero re-spend on reused; failure ≠ abstention; completeness guard rejects an
+  incomplete matrix).
+- `decide_083` on the cheap-validate = **NOT_REACHED, blocked_by="eu7"** — the honest
+  current eu7 point = 0.896 < the 0.90 floor (design §5). The eu7 hard-gate fires
+  before the power guard; this is the correct mechanical output, not the parity gap.
+
+### Cost gate (the phase-gate decision) — projected full run EXCEEDS $20 at the pilot config
+
+Per-(question×arm) call = **$0.026925** (input-token-dominated; ~21.5k prompt tokens
+from long LME sessions). **Projected full = $0.026925 × 606 × 3 ≈ $48.95 → NOT ≤ $20**
+(and over the aggregate $30 program budget). ≤$20 is reachable with a window-fit
+context budget ≤ ~32k chars (~$18) or k≤4 (~$20). See `STATUS-0.8.3.md` for the full
+lever table. **Phase B is BLOCKED on an orchestrator/HITL decision: authorize a
+reduced-context config or raise the budget.**
+
+### Comparator stand-up status
+
+- **Mem0-OSS: STOOD UP** (isolated env; `build_local_mem0_config` → airlock
+  qwen3.6-27b LLM + local bge-small + on-disk chroma, per-run isolated, no cloud).
+  Adapter made version-robust to mem0 2.x search API.
+- **Graphiti/Zep: BLOCKER (clean).** No local Neo4j/FalkorDB backend running and no
+  `graphiti_core` install; standing it up + a per-doc-extraction adapter is non-trivial.
+  Per design §3 Graphiti is the 2nd comparator (not a blocker on the Mem0 resolution);
+  the gap runs with {Mem0, naive-RAG}. Phase-B recipe in the Slice-10 output JSON.
+
+### Power note (expected at Phase B)
+
+The manifest implied-N proxy shows every class needs N ≫ 150 for paired MDE ≤ ε=0.05
+(factoid 524, knowledge_update 601, multi_session 768, temporal 752). At N=150 expect
+`decide_083 = NOT_REACHED underpowered:<class>` — **the per-class gap numbers still LAND
+(design §5) and the under-power triggers a HITL escalation (grow N vs accept), not
+suppression.**
+
+### The citable per-class gap (recall + accuracy, paired 95% CI) — **PENDING PHASE B**
+
+To be filled by the authorized resilient priced pass over the full 606-q gold.
